Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Florfenicol in Different Solvents at Temperatures from (278 to 318) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubilities of florfenicol in water, methanol, ethanol, acetone, tetrahydrofuran, 1-propanol, and water + acetone solvent mixtures from (278 to 318) K were measured with the mole fraction at atmospheric pressure. The light extinction method was used to determine the dissolution process. Results of these measurements were correlated with a semiempirical equation. For all systems, the semiempirical equation provided an accurate mathematical representation of the experimental data.
